The Victoria Cross (V.C.) is the highest honour available to 
Canadians and is awarded for the most conspicuous bravery, a 
daring or pre-eminent act of valour or self-sacrifice, or extreme 
devotion to duty in the presence of the enemy. The V.C. has 
been awarded to 96 Canadians since 1854.

 Alexander Roberts Dunn- 1st to be awarded VC.
